Teton Valley Criterium Series at Teton Reserve
description: Teton Valley Criterium Training Series Hosted by Teton Reserve in Victor Idaho.  Start Time=Wednesday Nights at 6:30.  Each Wednesday in July is a training ride with a competitive Final on Sat. Aug 2nd.
course: Teton Reserve\\\'s new asphalt winds through the greens of their beautifully landscaped golf resort. Courses get swept and alternate each week.
registration: Registration will be $20 day of for training rides.  Non USAC members $25.
notes: This is a USA Cycling permitted training series designed to provide a comfortable non intimidating venue to grow cycling skills and promote the sport of Cycling in the Teton Region.  Wed. night training rides will grow your skills in preparation for the Final on Sat. Aug 2nd.
directions: Teton Reserve is located between Driggs and Victor ID on 600 South about 1 mile East of ID State Route 33.  Parking is located at the Club House on the South side of 600 South.
